<p>Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said Ukraine will not hold national elections until a ceasefire is in place and the country has the security guarantees needed to run a safe vote, pushing back on suggestions that ballots could go ahead while the war continues. He also said there is no immediate plan to announce an election date, and that Ukraine would move toward elections only after those conditions are met. Ukraine remains under martial law, and the reporting notes the constitution does not allow national elections while martial law is in force.</p><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Term-and-feasibility context: Reporting noted Zelenskyy’s elected term has expired during the war, and that even some political opponents say today’s security and political conditions make an election impractical.</li><li>No date message: Zelenskyy said he has no near-term plan to announce an election date, and that Ukraine would move toward elections only once the conditions are met.</li><li>Pressure debate: CBS framed Zelenskyy’s remarks amid external political pressure from Donald Trump over elections, which Zelenskyy rejected as a basis for setting a date.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Volodymyr Zelenskyy: He said Ukraine would begin moving toward elections only after a ceasefire and the necessary security guarantees, and he said he has no plans to announce an election soon. (<a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/ukraine-russia-war-zelenskyy-no-plan-for-elections-despite-trump-pressure/'>CBS News</a>)</li><li>Ukrainian political opponents (as described): The reporting says even Zelenskyy’s opponents acknowledge current security and political conditions make holding an election impossible. (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/zelenskyy-says-ukraine-elections-can-only-be-held-after-ceasefire-13978819.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li><li>Euronews (legal framing): It said Ukraine’s constitution bars national elections while martial law is in force, which began on the day of Russia’s full-scale invasion. (<a href='http://www.euronews.com/2026/02/11/ukraine-will-only-hold-elections-after-security-guarantees-and-ceasefire-in-place-zelensky'>Euronews</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/ukraine-will-only-hold-elections-after-ceasefire-zelensky-says'>Ukraine will only hold elections after ceasefire, Zelensky says</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/zelenskyy-says-ukraine-elections-can-only-be-held-after-ceasefire-13978819.html'>Zelenskyy says Ukraine elections can only be held after ceasefire</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='http://www.euronews.com/2026/02/11/ukraine-will-only-hold-elections-after-security-guarantees-and-ceasefire-in-place-zelensky'>Ukraine will only hold elections after security guarantees and ceasefire in place, Zelenskyy says</a> - euronews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/ukraine-russia-war-zelenskyy-no-plan-for-elections-despite-trump-pressure/'>Zelenskyy denies plans to announce elections in Ukraine as war rages</a> - cbsnews.com</li></ul>